        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer336923221" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7241245404083411991">Loved it, loved it, loved it...did I mention - &quot;I loved it!&quot;<br/><br/>Kilted Desire – Sands of Betrayal<br/>by A.B. McKinley<br/><br/>Some authors tell stories, some paint pictures, A.B. McKinley draws us into his world of love, intrigue and betrayal. Right from his first words on paper you hear Scott’s accent, feel his embrace and sensual kisses with Katie, you feel the urgency when the bomb explodes in Iraq.<br/><br/>As our hearts pound through the streets of Baghdad, will Scott weave his way through the City and keep the woman</span>
  <span id="freeText7241245404083411991" style="display:none">Loved it, loved it, loved it...did I mention - "I loved it!"<br /><br />Kilted Desire – Sands of Betrayal<br />by A.B. McKinley<br /><br />Some authors tell stories, some paint pictures, A.B. McKinley draws us into his world of love, intrigue and betrayal. Right from his first words on paper you hear Scott’s accent, feel his embrace and sensual kisses with Katie, you feel the urgency when the bomb explodes in Iraq.<br /><br />As our hearts pound through the streets of Baghdad, will Scott weave his way through the City and keep the woman he is paid to keep safe out of harm’s way? <br /><br />Honor, Integrity and Charm would be the words I use to describe the main character, Scott Maclaren, as well as sexy, sensual and intriguing! This is a book for both sexes, men will love it as much for the sensual love scenes and all the “going’s on” in Baghdad’s Green Zone… a must read for the men too!<br /><br />Personally, I do not review all books I read… too many of them I guess. Kilted Desire – Sands of Betrayal is exceptional…I truly hated to turn the last page, I wanted to know more (a sign of an “exceptional” book) The author writes from his heart and soul… a refreshing and delightful combination. I hope this author continues to write for many, many years to come, I look forward to reading many more. <br /></span>
