<div id="review_524686176" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/524686176" />
    <a title="Renee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5727999-renee"><img alt="Renee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1378905230p2/5727999.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/524686176?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Renee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Renee" href="/user/show/5727999-renee">Renee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer524686176" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14509952236320083959">This was the first romance novel, written by a man, that I have read. I have to say I found it interesting to note the difference in perspective from what I am used to. The storyline in this book was intriguing and kept me turning pages in search of answers. It drew me in from the first chapter and flowed smoothly to the end - - - where I went HUH?????? I&apos;ll have to get the 2nd book for sure! <br/><br/>I love the characters of Scott and Katie and their bond. Not many people would be strong enough to withs</span>
  <span id="freeText14509952236320083959" style="display:none">This was the first romance novel, written by a man, that I have read. I have to say I found it interesting to note the difference in perspective from what I am used to. The storyline in this book was intriguing and kept me turning pages in search of answers. It drew me in from the first chapter and flowed smoothly to the end - - - where I went HUH?????? I'll have to get the 2nd book for sure! <br /><br />I love the characters of Scott and Katie and their bond. Not many people would be strong enough to withstand the trials they are subjected to. Scott is a definite alpha male, no nonsense, get the job done kind of guy and Katie appears to be his perfect match, as she is strong-willed, out-going, yet sweet and feminine, all at the same time. She is understanding, knows her man, and doesn't fight it.<br /><br />I would've liked a little more in-depth depiction of the relationship, but this goes back to perspective, I think. The important pieces are all here, just presented a bit differently than I am used to.<br /><br />All in all I enjoyed this book and will be reading the next one - - very soon. I think A.B. McKinley did a great job on his first book; I applaud him for taking on the romance genre, and I look forward to the continuation of this series and watching his talent develop even more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14509952236320083959" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


