<div id="review_419702832" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/419702832" />
    <a title="Sue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3477736-sue"><img alt="Sue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1320948914p2/3477736.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/419702832?book_show_action=true">Sep 22, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sue" href="/user/show/3477736-sue">Sue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/16039385-sands-of-betrayal">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=scottish">scottish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=sexy">sexy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=scotsman">scotsman</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=passionate">passionate</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=military">military</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=new-author">new-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=scots-american">scots-american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=kilted-warrior">kilted-warrior</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3477736-sue?shelf=kilted-hero">kilted-hero</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer419702832" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8328667181441318030">I really like this book. There is romance and action; passion and danger; and betrayal. If you like stories featuring rugged, military men I&apos;m sure you enjoy Kilted Desire. The hero Scott Maclaren is a former military man in the British Army. He moves to Ohio to stay with family while recuperating from injuries sustained while on duty in the war zone. While there, Scott meets and falls in love with Katie, a single mother with two kids. In order to be able to marry and live the kind of life Katie</span>
  <span id="freeText8328667181441318030" style="display:none">I really like this book. There is romance and action; passion and danger; and betrayal. If you like stories featuring rugged, military men I'm sure you enjoy Kilted Desire. The hero Scott Maclaren is a former military man in the British Army. He moves to Ohio to stay with family while recuperating from injuries sustained while on duty in the war zone. While there, Scott meets and falls in love with Katie, a single mother with two kids. In order to be able to marry and live the kind of life Katie wants, Scott goes to Bagdhad to work as a bodyguard. He is shocked when he finds out that his client is a sexy, red-haired woman. Britney decides she is going to seduce Scott because what Britney wants, Britney usually gets. Scott is not even aware of her plans as he is deeply in love with Katie and will stay true to the woman he loves. <br />There is a lot of action both in Iraq and in the bedroom. The scenes with Scott and Katie are hot, to say the least. And the action in Iraq is dangerous and scary to say the least. A.B.McKinley's writing makes you feel as if you are there with him and Britney as their car breaks down and they have to make their way back to the relative safety of their hotel. You can hear the glass crunch beneath their feet and share the fear as they make their way through the war torn street of Bagdhad. <br />I can not recommend Kilted Desire highly enough. There is enough romance to satisfy any romance reader and enough action in Bagdhad to satisfy anyone (male or female) who enjoys military action. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8328667181441318030" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


