              <span id="reviewTextContainer531143129" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10953714553026897144">Where&apos;s there a will, there a way.....And it was proven by all three main characters of the story, each in its own way with their own agenda (cause as much as I&apos;ve tried to ignore Britney, she is an integral part of the story). Yes, 5 stars for the reality of the story, for the clean lines and feelings, for the fact that the author showed Scott as a real person and not a superhero. I absolutely loved the intimate moments which can be cataloged as truly making love and not sex marathon, and that&apos;</span>
  <span id="freeText10953714553026897144" style="display:none">Where's there a will, there a way.....And it was proven by all three main characters of the story, each in its own way with their own agenda (cause as much as I've tried to ignore Britney, she is an integral part of the story). Yes, 5 stars for the reality of the story, for the clean lines and feelings, for the fact that the author showed Scott as a real person and not a superhero. I absolutely loved the intimate moments which can be cataloged as truly making love and not sex marathon, and that's complementing so well the story line and Scott's personality. I was enthralled, and couldn't help praying at some point when it became a little to painful..yup, that intense and captivating a story Kilted Desire is! I recommend it and is it in my re-read list and it goes in the favorites shelf. </span>
