              <span id="reviewTextContainer542848475" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer446984215982441429">The writing is unique. The author is from Scotland and it&apos;s written in a Scottish brogue. It is unlike anything I&apos;ve read before. You are with Scott in the middle of Baghdad, in a firefight. You are hiding in an alley facing down bad guys. This writer has it. He has lived it. You can feel what he feels and see what he sees. This book is for men as well as women. From being a bodyguard in Iraq to making love to his lady, this author has it.</span>
  <span id="freeText446984215982441429" style="display:none">The writing is unique. The author is from Scotland and it's written in a Scottish brogue. It is unlike anything I've read before. You are with Scott in the middle of Baghdad, in a firefight. You are hiding in an alley facing down bad guys. This writer has it. He has lived it. You can feel what he feels and see what he sees. This book is for men as well as women. From being a bodyguard in Iraq to making love to his lady, this author has it.</span>
